The paper discusses the comparison of citation counts for academic books using Microsoft Academic and Google Books, which involves information retrieval (IR) and natural language processing (NLP) techniques. The paper also mentions the fields of computer science, cybernetics (CY), and computational linguistics (CL) as some of the subject areas where Microsoft Academic found more citations than BKCI. Additionally, the paper's focus on citation analysis and impact assessment suggests a connection to digital libraries (DL) and machine learning (LG) sub-categories.
